    <item>
      <title>AutarcTech/Infinite Fingers Cluster Storage Announced</title>
      <link>http://www.infinitefingers.com/news/autarctech-infinite-fingers-cluster-storage-announced/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 26 Apr 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://www.infinitefingers.com/news/autarctech-infinite-fingers-cluster-storage-announced/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The past few months have been extremely productive. Our collaboration with &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.autarctech.de&#34;&gt;AutarcTech&lt;/a&gt;
is starting to produce some really positive results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Together we&amp;rsquo;ve taken their 48V Lithium battery balancing board, which has a limited range of applications,
added a bit of IT magic and transformed it into a an almost infinitely scaleable storage solution, perfect
for industrial applications.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As we are able to, we&amp;rsquo;ll share more information on the first application of this new product development.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Source: &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.pveurope.eu/News/Energy-Storage/AutarcTech-has-presented-cluster-storage-with-active-balancing-for-48-volt-batteries&#34;&gt;http://www.pveurope.eu/News/Energy-Storage/AutarcTech-has-presented-cluster-storage-with-active-balancing-for-48-volt-batteries&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
